bsoeApplyRedistribute.name: bsoeApplyRedistribute
bsoeApplyRedistribute.description: This object is used to implement the ospf 'ip ospf apply redistribute' command when the 'bgp|direct|rip|static' parameter is used. Setting it will cause the 'apply' to occur for the specified protocol. The value returned is always none(0).

bsoeHardwareCompatibilityMode.name: bsoeHardwareCompatibilityMode
bsoeHardwareCompatibilityMode.description: This object is used to set the 5510 hardware compatilibity mode.

bsoeOspfIfExtTable.name: bsoeOspfIfExtTable
bsoeOspfIfExtTable.description: Extensions to the ospfIfTable from RFC 1850.

bsoeOspfIfExtEntry.name: bsoeOspfIfExtEntry
bsoeOspfIfExtEntry.description: A set of objects that augments the ospfIfTable. There will be an entry in this table for each entry in the ospfIfTable.

bsoeOspfIfIpAddress.name: bsoeOspfIfIpAddress
bsoeOspfIfIpAddress.description: The IP address of this OSPF interface.

bsoeOspfAddressLessIf.name: bsoeOspfAddressLessIf
bsoeOspfAddressLessIf.description: For the purpose of easing the instancing of addressed and addressless interfaces; This variable takes the value 0 on interfaces with IP Addresses, and the corresponding value of ifIndex for interfaces having no IP Address.

bsoeOspfIfExtAdvertiseWhenDown.name: bsoeOspfIfExtAdvertiseWhenDown
bsoeOspfIfExtAdvertiseWhenDown.description: Equivalent to rcIpConfAdvertiseWhenDown (allows this flag to be accessed by interface IP rather than by ifIndex).

bsoeOspfIfExtPrimaryMd5Key.name: bsoeOspfIfExtPrimaryMd5Key
bsoeOspfIfExtPrimaryMd5Key.description: Primary key, if it exists. If there are no keys present, this object will be 0.

bsoeOspfIfExtMtuIgnore.name: bsoeOspfIfExtMtuIgnore
bsoeOspfIfExtMtuIgnore.description: Indicates whether to ignore mtu checking in ospf bdb.

bsoeOspfIfExtType.name: bsoeOspfIfExtType
bsoeOspfIfExtType.description: This object is an extension to the standard object ospfIfType. When the value of this object is other(1), then the type of the interface is given by ospfIfType. Otherwise, the value of this object indicates the type of the interface, and the value of ospfIfType is invalid. In the latter case, an implementation may simply not return the corresponding instance of ospfIfType.

bsoeMessageDigestTable.name: bsoeMessageDigestTable
bsoeMessageDigestTable.description: A table of message digest keys

bsoeMessageDigestIpAddress.name: bsoeMessageDigestIpAddress
bsoeMessageDigestIpAddress.description: The IP address of this OSPF interface.

bsoeMessageDigestAddressLessIf.name: bsoeMessageDigestAddressLessIf
bsoeMessageDigestAddressLessIf.description: For the purpose of easing the instancing of addressed and addressless interfaces; This variable takes the value 0 on interfaces with IP Addresses, and the corresponding value of ifIndex for interfaces having no IP Address.

bsoeMessageDigestIndex.name: bsoeMessageDigestIndex
bsoeMessageDigestIndex.description: An arbitrary index value for this digest value.

bsoeMessageDigestType.name: bsoeMessageDigestType
bsoeMessageDigestType.description: The type of digest value. Currently only MD5 is supported.

bsoeMessageDigestKey.name: bsoeMessageDigestKey
bsoeMessageDigestKey.description: The key value. When retrieved, the value is always an empty string. Setting this will change the key.

bsoeMessageDigestRowStatus.name: bsoeMessageDigestRowStatus
bsoeMessageDigestRowStatus.description: Controls creation and deletion of rows in this table. The value of bsoeMessageDigestKey must be set before a row can be made active. There are no restrictions on setting the value of bsoeMessageDigestKey while a row is active.

bsoeOspfNbrExtTable.name: bsoeOspfNbrExtTable
bsoeOspfNbrExtTable.description: Extensions to the ospfNbrTable from RFC 1850.

bsoeOspfNbrExtEntry.name: bsoeOspfNbrExtEntry
bsoeOspfNbrExtEntry.description: A set of objects that augments the ospfNbrTable. There will be an entry in this table for each entry in the ospfNbrTable.

bsoeOspfVirtIfExtTable.name: bsoeOspfVirtIfExtTable
bsoeOspfVirtIfExtTable.description: Extensions to the ospfVirtIfTable from RFC 1850.

bsoeOspfVirtIfExtEntry.name: bsoeOspfVirtIfExtEntry
bsoeOspfVirtIfExtEntry.description: A set of objects that augments the ospfVirtIfTable. There will be an entry in this table for each entry in the ospfVirtIfTable.

bsoeOspfVirtIfExtAreaId.name: bsoeOspfVirtIfExtAreaId
bsoeOspfVirtIfExtAreaId.description: The Transit Area that the Virtual Link traverses. By definition, this is not 0.0.0.0

bsoeOspfVirtIfExtNeighbor.name: bsoeOspfVirtIfExtNeighbor
bsoeOspfVirtIfExtNeighbor.description: The Router ID of the Virtual Neighbor.

bsoeOspfVirtIfExtPrimaryMd5Key.name: bsoeOspfVirtIfExtPrimaryMd5Key
bsoeOspfVirtIfExtPrimaryMd5Key.description: Primary key, if it exists. If there are no keys present, this object will be 0.

bsoeOspfVirtIfExtType.name: bsoeOspfVirtIfExtType
bsoeOspfVirtIfExtType.description: This object indicates whether the virtual link was created manually or automatically.

bsoeVirtIfMessageDigestTable.name: bsoeVirtIfMessageDigestTable
bsoeVirtIfMessageDigestTable.description: A table of message digest keys for virtual interfaces

bsoeVirtIfMessageDigestEntry.name: bsoeVirtIfMessageDigestEntry
bsoeVirtIfMessageDigestEntry.description: A message digest key for a virtual interface

bsoeVirtIfMessageDigestAreaId.name: bsoeVirtIfMessageDigestAreaId
bsoeVirtIfMessageDigestAreaId.description: The Transit Area that the Virtual Link traverses. By definition, this is not 0.0.0.0

bsoeVirtIfMessageDigestNeighbor.name: bsoeVirtIfMessageDigestNeighbor
bsoeVirtIfMessageDigestNeighbor.description: The Router ID of the Virtual Neighbor.

bsoeVirtIfMessageDigestIndex.name: bsoeVirtIfMessageDigestIndex
bsoeVirtIfMessageDigestIndex.description: An arbitrary index value for this digest value.

bsoeVirtIfMessageDigestType.name: bsoeVirtIfMessageDigestType
bsoeVirtIfMessageDigestType.description: The type of digest value. Currently only MD5 is supported.

bsoeVirtIfMessageDigestKey.name: bsoeVirtIfMessageDigestKey
bsoeVirtIfMessageDigestKey.description: The key value. When retrieved, the value is always an empty string. Setting this will change the key.

bsoeVirtIfMessageDigestRowStatus.name: bsoeVirtIfMessageDigestRowStatus
bsoeVirtIfMessageDigestRowStatus.description: Controls creation and deletion of rows in this table. The value of bsoeVirtIfMessageDigestKey must be set before a row can be made active. There are no restrictions on setting the value of bsoeVirtIfMessageDigestKey while a row is active.
